headline: Why Western Alliance Bancorporation (WAL) Shares Are Sliding Today
summary: Shares of regional banking company Western Alliance Bancorporation (NYSE:WAL) fell 3.1% in the afternoon session after reports revealed its exposure to the collapse of auto-parts supplier First Brands Group through a fund linked to Jefferies Financial Group.
